cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the deployment of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) as temporary flying base stations (BSs) to complement ground cellular systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a novel learning approach based on the weighted expectation maximization (WEM) algorithm to estimate the user distribution and the downlink traffic demand, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper formulates an optimization problem to deploy an optimal UAV onto the hotspot area in a way that the utilities of the overloaded ground BSs are maximized, which involves information theory concepts. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses the framework of contract theory to develop a traffic offload contract between the BS and UAV operators, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a novel learning approach based on the weighted expectation maximization (WEM) algorithm, which is a machine learning technique.
